    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-04T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-04T18:00:00-05:00" n="221"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d221">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">814.24/401: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Drew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-04T17:00:00-06:00"
                            >February 4, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>57. For Parkhurst Board of Economic Warfare<note n="24" xml:id="d221fn24">George
                        V. Parkhurst, Deputy Chief, Country Program Branch.</note> and Ravndal of
                    the Department<note n="25" xml:id="d221fn25">Christian M. Ravndal, Chief of the
                        Division of Exports and Requirements.</note> from Dall [<hi rend="italic"
                        >Dalley</hi>] and Moseley.<note n="26" xml:id="d221fn26">J. A. R. Dalley and
                        Harold W. Moseley, the former representing the Board of Economic Warfare and
                        the latter, the American Hemisphere Exports Office, were assigned to assist
                        in inaugurating a decentralized export control plan.</note> Mission and
                    Country Agency<note n="27" xml:id="d221fn27">The Guatemalan office responsible
                        for administering import controls.</note> will be ready to put
                    Decentralization Plan “A”<note n="28" xml:id="d221fn28">For an outline of the
                        plan, see circular airgram, January 19, 8 p.m., <ref target="#pg_106">p.
                            106</ref>.</note> into effect for all materials on April 1. Beginning
                    March 1 preference requests will be issued in lieu of Certificates of Necessity
                    on allocated materials for second quarter. It is suggested that outstanding
                    Certificates of Necessity be honored until April 30. Thenceforth all
                    applications for export license should be accompanied by preference
                    requests.</p>
                <p>Send timing and recapitulation of all materials under quota and CMP<note n="29"
                        xml:id="d221fn29">Controlled Materials Plan; for an explanation of this
                        plan, see circular instruction of April 26, <ref target="#pg_111">p.
                            111</ref>.</note> with full instructions and estimate of supply.</p>
                <p>No great difficulty is anticipated in Guatemala in the operation of this plan.
                    [Dalley and Moseley.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Drew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
